Damon Muller was diagnosed with Juvenile Dermatomyositis (JDM) in November . 
  It is a rare autoimmune disease that can only be treated with high doses of steroids and a chemotherapy-type drug . 
  Damon has almost doubled in size due to swelling and bloating as a result of his medication . 
  He can't go out in the sun and his throat can swell so much it almost closes over . 
  The disease has robbed him of the ability to run and ride his bike . 
  He was diagnosed after he developed bright red rashes on his legs and body . 
 